Quadri Aruna has started the New Year as the top 14th player in the latest ITTF rankings even as he inspired his German club TTC RhönSprudel Fulda-Maberzell (TTC) to a comeback win at the weekend. After their disappointing 3-0 loss to Borussia Dusseldorf in the semifinal of the German Cup, Aruna returned TTC to winning ways in the Table Tennis Bundesliga (TTBL). Aruna had in the, meantime, ended 2021 as the top 15th player in the men’s ranking by the world table tennis ruling body. In the TTBL and after winning the first leg 3-1 at home against TTF Liebherr Ochsenhausen, TTC again restored their superiority over their host with strong individual performances from Ruwen Filus, Aruna, and Alexandre Cassin.   Pele warns Super Eagles on Gambia     AFCON: prelims wrap up on GOtv, DStv     NGF hails oldest golfer Pa Omolaso   It was Filus, who started the match against Ochsenhausen’s top player Simon Gauzy but he spirited to a well-deserved 3 -1 (11-9, 11-8, 8-11, 11-5) victory for the visitors. - Advertisement - Ditto for Aruna who made a short work of American Kanak Jha in a flattering 3-0 (11-6, 11-5, 11-4) win. TTC’s Frenchman Cassin then closed the tie in an exciting five-set thriller against Samuel Kulczycki. Though the young Frenchman giving up the first set, he was already 7:9 behind in the second, before he turned up and secured the equalizer with four points in a row and catapulted back into the game. The last two sets were 11-5 and 11-4 for Cassin. The victory, helped TTC move past Ochsenhausen in the table and with a spot in the playoff race.